                                                    <p class="mb-4 size-18">The mission of our Sport Management bachelor’s degree program is to prepare our students to become reflective, principled, knowledgeable and creative learners who will succeed in the global sport management community in the 21st century.</p>
                                                    <p class="mb-4 size-18">The Sport Management B.S. degree program at Marshall University will teach you the latest methods and strategies for business communication, sport marketing, sport finance and economics, sport law, ethical and legal issues in sport business, facility management and more. You’ll also develop problem-solving and decision-making skills, sharpen written and oral communications, and your computer proficiency, and be able to conduct independent research and analysis.</p>
                                                    <p class="mb-4 size-18">In our Sport Management program, you’ll also gain firsthand experience by completing multiple semesters for fieldwork and internships in real sport business settings. This experience will help you gain not only valuable experience but also opportunities to network as you prepare to enter the workforce.</p>
